<p>GDP growth: 0.5% GDP: $344bn (PPP: $213bn) Inflation: 2.0% Population: 5.6m GDP per head: $61,340 (PPP: $38,040)</p>

<p>The centre-left ended the centre-right's three-term hold on power in late-2011 elections, with Helle Thorning-Schmidt becoming the country's first female prime minister. Her government is likely to boost public spending, financed by tax increases. Reforms of the labour and welfare codes inherited from the outgoing team will be continued, including tougher benefits criteria, a higher retirement age and a longer working week. The economy will barely grow as western Europe slumps badly.</p>

